{"TopicId":200710,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Backup files","CreatedByName":"marcast","CreatedById":207360,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-01T15:18:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"marcast","CreatedById":207360,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-01T15:18:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have the original game, no mods installed. In order to protect me by a HD crash, which files should I save? Is it enough to copy the \u0022KSP\\saves\u0022 folder?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-01T15:20:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYup, everything that\u0027s not replaceable will be inside that folder.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-01T15:30:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI recommend to copy the whole KSP folder, this way you don\u0027t have to worry about mods or any settings not copied. I do regular backups of my whole KSP folder every couple of\u00A0weeks plus when changing my installation (e.g. updating a mod), and I also make a backup of the \\saves folder every time I start KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBetter safe than sorry \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-03-01T15:35:15Z\u0022 title=\u002203/01/2021 03:35  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 1, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-01T17:04:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223933901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200710\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221614611934\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022207360\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022marcast\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, marcast said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have the original game, no mods installed. In order to protect me by a HD crash, which files should I save? Is it enough to copy the \u0022KSP\\saves\u0022 folder?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, and if you ponder space than cut the pre-installed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223933910\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200710\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221614612607\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI recommend to copy the whole KSP folder, this way you don\u0027t have to worry about mods or any settings not copied. I do regular backups of my whole KSP folder every couple of\u00A0weeks plus when changing my installation (e.g. updating a mod), and I also make a backup of the \\saves folder every time I start KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBetter safe than sorry \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDepends a bit on your personal view of quantity vs quality \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEverything except the saves can be easily downloaded and restored\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI backup my saves as part of my startup script.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd note that the save files are all text, so they are highly compressible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-01T17:30:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223933948\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200710\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221614618263\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Curveball Anders\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, Curveball Anders said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEverything except the saves can be easily downloaded and restored\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSettings... from settings.cfg, to the various .xml from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E, to\u00A0toolbar-settings.dat,\u00A0JanitorsCloset.dat, ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose are the ones always costing me the most time when starting from scratch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-01T18:00:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223933964\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200710\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221614619821\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSettings... from settings.cfg, to the various .xml from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, to\u00A0toolbar-settings.dat,\u00A0JanitorsCloset.dat, ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose are the ones always costing me the most time when starting from scratch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRight, I\u0027ll add the .cfg files to my script.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-01T18:02:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nor just \u0022robocopy \u0026lt;source\u0026gt;\u00A0\u0026lt;dest\u0026gt;\u00A0/mir\u0022 ? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-01T18:32:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223933990\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200710\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221614621737\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nor just \u0022robocopy \u0026lt;source\u0026gt;\u00A0\u0026lt;dest\u0026gt;\u00A0/mir\u0022 ? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfind or rsync, I\u0027m fully Linux since years back \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-01T19:02:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223934001\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200710\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221614623561\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Curveball Anders\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, Curveball Anders said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m fully Linux since years back\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m too dumb for that \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}